article.headline: Southern Utah 69, Western Illinois 53
article.story: CEDAR CITY, Utah (AP) -- Brothers Nate and Rand Janes each scored 16 points and Nate Janes grabbed 10 rebounds to lead Southern Utah to a 69-53 victory over Western Illinois Thursday night. Henry Uhegwu scored 12 points for the Thunderbirds (4-14, 3-3 Mid-Continent), and Fernando Bonfirm added 11. Eliz Cepeda led Western Illinois (5-12, 1-5) with 12 points, and Fred Oguns scored 11. Oguns went 9-10 from the foul line. Southern Utah opened the game with a 17-2 run, during which Nate Janes scored nine points on four baskets. Western Illinois responded with an 11-4 run, highlighted by a dunk and a 3-pointer by Sean Blalock, that cut the lead to 21-13 with 8:35 left in the half. Southern Utah scored the next 13 points, taking a 34-13 lead on David Marek s 3-pointer with 4:38 to play in the half. Western Illinois cut the lead to 39-29 by halftime, but Rand Janes hit two 3-pointers and Bonfirm made three layups off the offensive board to spark the Thunderbirds to a 12-2 run to begin the second half. Southern Utah held David Jackson, the Leathernecks' leading scorer at 15.1 points per game, to two field goals and nine points. The Janes brothers shot a combined 13-16 from the field, including 5-5 from 3-point range, and had nine of the Thunderbirds' 21 assists. The Thunderbirds played without leading scorer Lubor Olsovsky, who sat out a one-game suspension by the school for unsportsmanlike behavior after a loss Saturday at Centenary.
